=Description=

"How can the economic and sociological theories of the commons serve as a lens for reconsidering art and design education while rethinking their institutional structures? Given the intersection of contemporary commons theories and free open-source culture, how might the relationship between code and the commons inform a critical reevaluation of spaces, tools, and methodologies for transmitting and sharing knowledge? These are the questions addressed in this research."

